<p>I‚Äôm currently in a role in which I have to navigate and explore a lot of new SQL tables that I‚Äôm not familiar with, so I found myself typing ‚Äúselect * from ‚Ä¶ limit 100‚Äù over and over again. I finally decided to automate that phrase such that if I typed ‚Äússs‚Äù it would automatically type ‚Äúselect * from  limit 100‚Äù. I couldn‚Äôt be happier with the results. This is how I did it:</p>

<p>I used the program AutoHotKey ‚Äî my company had this in their software library so I installed it via that.</p>

<p>My script looks like this:</p>
